Ted Odogwu, Kano The majority leader of the Kano State House of Assembly, Alhaji Labaran Abdul-Madari, was on Wednesday, removed from office by his colleagues His erstwhile deputy, Alhaji Kabiru Hassan-Dashi, was immediately announced as his replacement. It was gathered that Abdul-Madari’s removal followed a motion of urgent public importance, moved by Alhaji Muhammad Uba-Gurjiya (APC, Bunkure) and properly seconded. The session was presided over by the Speaker, Abdulazeez Garba-Gafasa. Of the 28 APC lawmakers in the 40-member house, 23 unanimously supported the motion, which was seconded by Alhaji Ali Ibrahim-Shanono (APC Bagwai/Shanono). Moments after the majority leader’s removal, Alhaji Hamza Massu (APC Sumaila Constituency) was nominated and elected Deputy Majority Leader. Copyright PUNCH.
